#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:1
msgid "vtkPolyDataNormals: Split into separate classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:3
msgid ""
"`vtkPolyDataNormals` used to be a single class that performed, splitting of "
"strips, orienting polygons, splitting sharp edges, and computing normals. "
"This class has been split as follows to make it easier to use and understand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:7
msgid ""
"`vtkTriangleFilter` now has an option to `PreservePolys`, so that only "
"strips can be split."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:8
msgid "`vtkOrientPolyData` is a new class that orients polygons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:9
msgid "`vtkSplitSharpEdgesPolyData` is a new class that splits sharp edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:10
msgid "`vtkPolyDataNormals` now only computes point and cell normals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:12
msgid ""
"The new classes are more efficient and easier to use and read than the old "
"`vtkPolyDataNormals` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:14
msgid ""
"Additionally, `vtkAbstractCellLinks` now also have `ShallowCopy` which is "
"used to copy the cell links to avoid copying/rebuilding them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:17
msgid ""
"Moreover, `vtkStaticCellLinks`'s BuildLinks for `vtkPolyData` has been fixed "
"and multi-threaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/split-vtkPolyDataNormals.md:19
msgid ""
"Finally, `vtkPolyData` when `Editable` is Off, `vtkStaticCellLinks` is used "
"to create the cell links."
msgstr ""
